# Mosfet Topologies
is a collection of jupyter notebooks (.ipynb) that serve as a form of a blog that aims as a repository of knowledge of Mosfet Topologies for use in Analog and Digital Design. Showcasing not only the theory of Topology but also the results from real SPICE simulations of the topology using real device models and measurements from said simulations via [PySpice](https://pyspice.fabrice-salvaire.fr/examples/index.html) which is a NgSpice Wrapper that allows for SPICE circuit generation and simulation using python. 

The file that can be viewed on GitHub website and downloaded (information coming on how to) and used as an exploration tool is [AnalogMOSFET_Tobologies.ipynb](https://github.com/PyLCARS/PySpiceExsamples/blob/master/MosfetTopologies/AnalogMOSFET_Tobologies.ipynb). Where below are some the results of a Resistor Loaded Common Source Amplifier
